The paper presents a new methodology that combines neural networks with functional analysis to estimate the solutions of partial differential equations. This methodology involves optimization and unsupervised learning, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks as the free function, which is a common approach in numerical analysis and scientific computing (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper presents a new way of transforming PDEs into unconstrained optimization problems, which involves functional analysis and constrained expressions (cs.SI, cs.CE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.CE.
